<hw>Per"ron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>An out-of-door flight of steps, as in a garden, leading to a terrace or to an upper story; -- usually applied to medi⟦ae⟧vel or later structures of some architectural pretensions.</def>⟦br⟧
